SMART Indicator Report: Thermal Habitat Area

Indicator category

[Fill by hand, needs decision by Council]

Indicator name

Thermal Habitat Area

Includes variable(s): >0.5C GLORYS, >1.5C GLORYS, >1C GLORYS, >10.5C GLORYS, >10C GLORYS, >11.5C GLORYS, >11C GLORYS, >12.5C GLORYS, >12C GLORYS, >13.5C GLORYS, >13C GLORYS, >14.5C GLORYS, >14C GLORYS, >15.5C GLORYS, >15C GLORYS, >16.5C GLORYS, >16C GLORYS, >17.5C GLORYS, >17C GLORYS, >18.5C GLORYS, >18C GLORYS, >19.5C GLORYS, >19C GLORYS, >2.5C GLORYS, >2C GLORYS, >20.5C GLORYS, >20C GLORYS, >21.5C GLORYS, >21C GLORYS, >22.5C GLORYS, >22C GLORYS, >23.5C GLORYS, >23C GLORYS, >24.5C GLORYS, >24C GLORYS, >25.5C GLORYS, >25C GLORYS, >26.5C GLORYS, >26C GLORYS, >27.5C GLORYS, >27C GLORYS, >28.5C GLORYS, >28C GLORYS, >29.5C GLORYS, >29C GLORYS, >3.5C GLORYS, >3C GLORYS, >30C GLORYS, >4.5C GLORYS, >4C GLORYS, >5.5C GLORYS, >5C GLORYS, >6.5C GLORYS, >6C GLORYS, >7.5C GLORYS, >7C GLORYS, >8.5C GLORYS, >8C GLORYS, >9.5C GLORYS, >9C GLORYS

Indicator brief description

Calculates the proportion of each EPU that exceeds temperature thresholds as a daily time series from 1993 2024

Indicator visualization

For each EPU, bottom temperature data were separated by depth bin (0-25m; 25m-100m; and >100m), as well as temperature threshold (>15C , >24C), and the proportion of each EPU exceeding these thresholds was calculated on a daily basis from 1993 to 2024. Time series of each years proportional area show an increasing proportion of the MAB and GB mid-depths have experienced high temperatures in recent years. The 24C threshold is rarely seen in GB and GOM.

Indicator documentation

Indicator analysis/testing or history of use

What decision or advice processes are the indicators currently used in?

See Thermal Habitat Persistence for cell-based calculations. Many deep water benthic and demersal species exhibit thermal preferences for metabolic, reproductive, and growth processes. Temperatures above these thermal preferences may impair these processes. Two temperature thresholds (15 and 24 degrees C) were chosen based on cutoff points where demersal species are less commonly found. Thermal habitat area is calculated by identifying 1/12 degree cells within a given EPU that are greater than or equal to the temperature threshold then taking the sum of all cell areas. Data from 1993-01-01 to 2024-09-10 were obtained from the CMEMS GLORYS12V1 global reanalysis product.

What implications of the indicators are currently listed?

If a large proportion of species current habitat become thermally inhospitable, it can influence species productivity and in, extreme cases, cause mortality.
